This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it focuses on understanding network probing traffic and enhancing defense strategies. The cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category is also likely as the paper deals with network traffic analysis. The cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category is a possibility as the paper studies the behavior of network probers. The cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category is a possibility as the paper uses models to predict port probing rates. The cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category is a possibility as the paper performs exploratory data analysis.
